// KNOWN LIMITATION (pinned, not fixed here): naming a union primary-
// constructor parameter `value` (or `has_value`) makes the variant
// uncompilable. `Symbols.VARIANT.find_member` hides those two names
// from variant scope unconditionally to preserve the legacy
// default-variant accessor pattern (`u.value` / `u!`). With this
// feature the synthesised structural-equality and hash methods on
// each variant reference every spliced field through `self.<name>`
// / `other.<name>`; with the inherited field hidden from variant
// scope, those references fail with "member value not found in
// <variant>".
//
// Workaround today: avoid `value` / `has_value` as primary-param
// names on a union.
//
// Correct resolution would be to scope the exclusion to unions that
// actually have a default variant. Needs a flag plumbed from the
// default-variant detection (AST-side) through to the union symbol
// so find_member can gate on it; left for a follow-up PR.

union HOLDER(value: int) is
    BOX(payload: string, ..);
    BAG(items: int, ..);
si

entry() is
si
